In [352]:
# plotting a bar chart for gender vs total amount

sales_gen = df.groupby(['Gender'], as_index=False)['Amount'].sum().sort_values(by='Amount', ascending=False)
sns.barplot(x = 'Gender',y= 'Amount' ,data = sales_gen, color='maroon')
plt.title("Gender vs Total Amount")
plt.show()

The data presented in the graphs reveals that the majority of buyers are female, and their overall spending surpasses that of male consumers.

In [124]:
# Total Amount vs Age Group
sales_age = df.groupby(['Age Group'], as_index=False)['Amount'].sum().sort_values(by='Amount', ascending=False)

sns.barplot(x = 'Age Group',y= 'Amount' ,data = sales_age, hue ='Age Group')
plt.title("Total Amount vs Age Group")
plt.show()

The data visualized in the graphs demonstrates a clear trend: the most significant portion of the customer base consists of females within the 26-35 age bracket.

State

In [174]:
# total number of orders from top 10 states

sales_state = df.groupby(['State'], as_index=False)['Orders'].sum().sort_values(by='Orders', ascending=False).head(10)

sns.set(rc={'figure.figsize':(10,5)})
ax= sns.barplot(data = sales_state, x = 'State',y= 'Orders', hue = 'State')
plt.xticks(rotation =45)
for bars in ax.containers:
    ax.bar_label(bars)
plt.title('Total number of orders from top 10 states')
plt.show()
In [176]:
# total amount/sales from top 10 states

sales_state = df.groupby(['State'], as_index=False)['Amount'].sum().sort_values(by='Amount', ascending=False).head(10)

sns.set(rc={'figure.figsize':(15,5)})
ax=sns.barplot(data = sales_state, x = 'State',y= 'Amount', hue= 'State')
plt.xticks(rotation =45)
plt.title('Total Amount/Sales from top 10 states')
plt.show()

From above graphs we can see that most of the orders & total sales/amount are from Uttar Pradesh, Maharashtra and Karnataka respectively

In [233]:
#Marital status alog with sales 
sales_state = df.groupby(['Marital_Status', 'Gender'], as_index=False)['Amount'].sum().sort_values(by='Amount', ascending=False)

sns.set(rc={'figure.figsize':(6,5)})
sns.barplot(data = sales_state, x = 'Marital_Status',y= 'Amount', hue='Gender')
plt.title('Marital Status VS Sales')
plt.show()

Married women are the dominant consumer group and possess higher purchasing capabilities, as evidenced by the data.

Occupation

In [283]:
# Analysis of the occupation of the customers
sns.set(rc={'figure.figsize':(20,10)})
ax = sns.countplot(data = df, x = 'Occupation', hue='Occupation')

for bars in ax.containers:
    ax.bar_label(bars, fontsize= 20)
    plt.xticks(rotation =45, fontsize=20)
    plt.xlabel('Occupation', fontsize=20)
    plt.ylabel('Count', fontsize=20)
    plt.title('Occupation wise Distribution of customers', fontsize=35)
In [285]:
sales_state = df.groupby(['Occupation'], as_index=False)['Amount'].sum().sort_values(by='Amount', ascending=False)

sns.set(rc={'figure.figsize':(20,10)})
sns.barplot(data = sales_state, x = 'Occupation',y= 'Amount', hue='Occupation')
plt.xticks(rotation =45, fontsize=20)
plt.xlabel('Occupation', fontsize=20)
plt.ylabel('Amount', fontsize=20)
plt.title('Sales grouped by Occupation',fontsize=35)
plt.show()

A predominant portion of the buyer base is comprised of individuals working in the IT, healthcare, and aviation sectors, as evidenced by the graphs.

In [315]:
#Sales as per product category
sales_state = df.groupby(['Product_Category'], as_index=False)['Amount'].sum().sort_values(by='Amount', ascending=False).head(10)

sns.set(rc={'figure.figsize':(20,5)})
sns.barplot(data = sales_state, x = 'Product_Category',y= 'Amount',hue='Product_Category')

plt.yticks(fontsize=20)
plt.xlabel('Product Category', fontsize=28)
plt.ylabel('Amount', fontsize=28)
plt.title('Sales based Product Category',fontsize=35)
plt.show()

Food, Clothing, and Electronics emerge as the dominant product categories based on sales data.

# top 10 most sold products (same thing as above)

fig1, ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize=(8,7))
df.groupby('Product_ID')['Orders'].sum().nlargest(10).sort_values(ascending=False).plot(kind='bar' ,color='red')
plt.title('Top 10 most sold products',fontsize=20)
plt.show()

CONCLUSION

ZMarried women within the age bracket of 26 to 35, residing in the states of Uttar Pradesh, Maharashtra, and Karnataka, and employed in the IT, healthcare, or aviation sectors, exhibit a pronounced propensity forpurchasing products from the food, clothing, and electronics categories.
